HEADWORD: Amphibrach
<hw>Am"phi*brach</hw> <pr>(⟦acr⟧m"f⟦icr⟧*br⟦acr⟧k)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[L. <?/, Gr. <?/ short at both ends; <grk>'amfi`</grk> +
<grk>brachy`s</grk> short.]</ety> <fld>(Anc. Pros.)</fld> <def>A foot of
three syllables, the middle one long, the first and last short (⟦cre⟧ --
⟦cre⟧); as, <xex>h⟦acr⟧b⟦emac⟧r⟦ecr⟧</xex>. In modern prosody the
accented syllable takes the place of the long and the unaccented of the
short; as, <xex>pro-phet⟦bprime⟧ic</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

